# PRASANTH - CRM Showcase Landing Page Edits

This file tracks every single edit made to the `showcase` landing page in detail. The landing page is built using pure HTML, CSS (Tailwind via CDN), and Vanilla JavaScript, located entirely within the `showcase/` directory.

## Current Edits

* **Research Phase**: Identified the current tech stack. The landing page located at `showcase/` is built using pure HTML, CSS, and vanilla JS. It does *not* use React or Next.js (unlike the `frontend/` directory). To comply with the strict instruction of not adding any new tech stack, all animations and layout updates will be implemented using Vanilla JS and Tailwind CSS.
* **Edit 1 (`showcase/index.html`)**: Updated the Google Font import from `Inter` to `Outfit` to give the page a more geometric, premium feel. Added the HTML DOM elements `<div class="cursor-dot"></div>` and `<div class="cursor-outline"></div>` immediately after the `body` tag to serve as the custom Antigravity-style mouse cursor. Updated the Tailwind config within the file to use `Outfit` as the default sans font.
* **Edit 2 (`showcase/styles.css`)**: Removed the default browser cursor by adding `cursor: none;` to the global `html` and `body` rules, as well as to all interactive elements (`a`, `button`, `.feature-card`, etc.). Added detailed CSS styling for `.cursor-dot` (a solid brand-colored circle) and `.cursor-outline` (a larger, semi-transparent circle with a border) with fixed positioning and CSS transitions for size, color, and transform changes. Defined a `.cursor-outline.hover` state that expands the cursor and changes its background opacity to create a "magnetic" or "focus" effect over clickable elements.
* **Edit 3 (`showcase/script.js`)**: Injected a new JavaScript block within the `DOMContentLoaded` event. Created a continuous rendering loop using `requestAnimationFrame` that tracks the real-time `clientX` and `clientY` coordinates. The dot follows the mouse instantly, while the outline uses a mathematical easing function (linear interpolation) to smoothly trail behind it. Finally, added event listeners (`mouseenter` and `mouseleave`) to all interactive elements to trigger the expanded hover state on the custom cursor.

## Phase 2: Complete Structural Rewrite (Antigravity Style)

* **Design Concept**: Scrapped the dark-mode grid layout in favor of a pristine, minimalist light theme mirroring the Antigravity reference. Focus shifted to massive typography, negative space, and section-by-section pacing.
* **Edit 4 (`showcase/index.html`)**: Performed a total rewrite of the HTML structure. Changed the global theme to `bg-[#f8f9fa] text-[#111827]`. Replaced the busy hero section with an ultra-clean, massive typography hero (`text-9xl tracking-tighter`). Restructured the 27 features into elegant, sticky-scrolling minimalist blocks. Replaced colorful AI visualizer bubbles with sleek, monochrome wireframe-style representations.
* **Edit 5 (`showcase/styles.css`)**: Removed all neon glows, gradient orbs, and dark-mode artifacts. Updated the custom cursor (`.cursor-dot` and `.cursor-outline`) to use stark black (`#000000`) and subtle gray tones, ensuring high contrast against the light theme.
* **Edit 6 (`showcase/script.js`)**: Cleaned up legacy parallax code that relied on the removed gradient orbs. Enhanced smooth scrolling and intersection observers for the new massive typography fade-ins.

## Phase 3: Content Restoration & Grammar Polish

* **Edit 7 (`showcase/index.html`)**: Restored the missing content sections (Video Demo, Roles, Tech Stack, and Stats) from the original dark-mode site, meticulously adapting them to the new Antigravity light theme with minimalist borders and massive typography.
* **Edit 8 (`showcase/index.html`)**: Expanded the "Engine" feature pillars to comprehensively list all 27 original CRM features, ensuring no content was lost during the structural redesign.
* **Edit 9 (`showcase/index.html`)**: Polished the grammar in the hero section ("A completely redesigned approach to SEO management, featuring 27 powerful tools...") and the footer CTA for a highly professional tone.
* **Edit 10 (`showcase/script.js`)**: Injected an `IntersectionObserver` to monitor the restored Stats section, bringing back the smooth 0-to-target number counting animation when the user scrolls down to that area.
* **Edit 11 (`showcase/index.html`)**: Increased the font size of the 5 navbar links from `text-sm` to `text-lg` for better readability.
* **Edit 12 (`showcase/index.html`)**: Replaced the static video placeholder image with a live looping, muted video. Added two prominent call-to-action buttons directly below the video ("Explore Features" and "View Stats") that adhere to the light/dark minimalist color palette.

## Phase 4: Grid Restoration & Monochrome Iconography

* **Edit 13 (`showcase/index.html`)**: Completely removed the Video section and relocated the "Explore Features" and "View Stats" buttons directly up into the Hero section for immediate accessibility.
* **Edit 14 (`showcase/index.html`)**: Restructured "The Engine" section from a text-based layout back to a 3-column animated grid showcasing the top 15+ CRM features. Implemented strict black-and-white glassmorphic styling for the feature cards and their internal mockups, completely removing the original colorful gradients.
* **Edit 15 (`showcase/index.html`)**: Executed a global removal of all colorful emojis across the entire project (in the Features, AI Brain, Roles, and Tech Stack sections). Replaced them entirely with professional, minimalist SVG icons to strictly adhere to the premium Antigravity light/dark theme constraint.
* **Edit 16 (`showcase/index.html`)**: Restored the Sticky Scroll layout for "The Engine" section, pinning the massive typography header to the left side while the grid of 15 features scrolls smoothly on the right.
* **Edit 17 (`showcase/index.html`)**: Drastically enhanced the "AI Brain" section by changing its background to stark black for contrast, and implementing a dynamic, animated glowing data pipeline (`@keyframes data-flow`) that visually passes through the nodes.
* **Edit 18 (`showcase/index.html`)**: Redesigned the "Four Roles" section into a premium, interactive hover-expand accordion (flex layout transitions), where hovering over a role expands its card and reveals its description seamlessly.
* **Edit 19 (`showcase/index.html`)**: Adjusted the Engine section to be sticky horizontally at the top with a blurred glassmorphic background (`backdrop-blur`), allowing the feature grids to scroll underneath it.
* **Edit 20 (`showcase/index.html`)**: Decreased the vertical height of the Four Roles accordion cards to create a more square, balanced proportion on desktop, and optimized the layout for mobile responsiveness (`flex-col` with disabled hover-expansion on touch devices).
* **Edit 21 (`showcase/script.js`, `showcase/index.html`)**: Re-engineered the Hero Section Particle System into a "Magnetic Grid." Black dots are aligned in a perfect grid and remain completely invisible. The user's cursor acts as a North Pole magnet, revealing and physically repelling the dots outward into a circular form around the cursor using smooth spring physics.
* **Edit 22 (`showcase/script.js`, `showcase/index.html`, `showcase/styles.css`)**: Added advanced scroll logic to the Navbar to trigger a glassmorphic background blur only when scrolling down. Removed the "Log In" button on mobile and introduced a clean animated Hamburger menu. When the mobile menu opens, the 5 core sections beautifully cascade in with a staggered upward-sliding animation, automatically redirecting and closing when tapped.
* **Edit 23 (`showcase/styles.css`, `showcase/index.html`)**: Fully optimized for mobile screens. Relocated the Engine sub-header text to the bottom of the section and completely disabled custom trailing cursors on mobile screens to restore native touch usability.
* **Edit 24 (`showcase/index.html`)**: Fixed a CSS clipping bug on mobile devices where the `backdrop-blur` on the scrolling navbar was trapping the fixed-position mobile menu overlay. Completely disabled the magnetic grid particle animation on mobile devices (`hidden lg:block`) as requested, ensuring the high-performance animation runs exclusively on desktop.

